<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F1EFE9048F75030FB51F86F" pageId="336" pageNumber="337" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="007606418F1EFE9048F75030FB51F86F" blockId="336.[151,1436,847,1951]" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1EFE9048F75030FE9EF8C4" bold="true" box="[199,315,1820,1844]" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">Remarks.</emphasis>
The hind tibia has one very long tibial spur and one tuft of bristles, among which one bristle is larger than others; it is not a second spur; for this reason, this species is included in 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F1EFE904C03506CFB3DF8A8" authorityName="Olmi 1984:" authorityYear="1126" box="[1075,1176,1856,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Adryinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="336" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1EFE904C03506CFB3DF8A8" box="[1075,1176,1856,1880]" italics="true" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">Adryinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not in 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F1EFE904D24506CFA30F8A8" authorityName="R. Perkins" authorityYear="1905" box="[1300,1429,1856,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Neodryinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="336" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1EFE904D24506CFA30F8A8" box="[1300,1429,1856,1880]" italics="true" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">Neodryinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F1EFE9048A75048FE91F88C" authorityName="Xu &amp; He" authorityYear="1995" box="[151,308,1892,1916]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Adryinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="336" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platycornis">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1EFE9048A75048FE91F88C" box="[151,308,1892,1916]" italics="true" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">A. platycornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here considered junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F1EFE904AD55048FC8FF88C" authorityName="Xu &amp; Yang" authorityYear="1995" box="[741,810,1892,1916]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Adryinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="336" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jini">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1EFE904AD55048FC8FF88C" box="[741,810,1892,1916]" italics="true" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">A. jini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, following the comparison of the types of both species. The small differences between the 
<specimenCount id="16CFCDC88F1EFE904A2E50A4FD19F86F" box="[542,700,1927,1951]" pageId="336" pageNumber="337" type="generic" typeStatus="holotypes">two holotypes</specimenCount>
do not justify the creation of two separate species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
